1
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:20,916
[NATSU] It's been too long!

2
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,625
Let's get back to work!

3
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:25,708
Whadda we got here?

4
00:00:25,791 --> 00:00:28,291
[HAPPY] Hey, how about
we give this one a try?

5
00:00:29,791 --> 00:00:31,875
So, all we gotta do is
capture this jail-breaker guy

6
00:00:31,958 --> 00:00:33,166
called Velveno?

7
00:00:33,250 --> 00:00:35,541
And they'll pay us
four million jewel?!

8
00:00:35,625 --> 00:00:37,083
Alright, now we're talkin'!

9
00:00:37,166 --> 00:00:39,416
I'm broke, and a huge
cash injection is just what

10
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:41,250
the doctor ordered!

11
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:46,291
♪

12
00:02:12,250 --> 00:02:14,083
[LUCY] What're we waiting for?

13
00:02:14,166 --> 00:02:16,375
We haven't decided
if we're taking it yet!

14
00:02:16,458 --> 00:02:18,458
Well, we sure could
use the money, too.

15
00:02:18,541 --> 00:02:20,000
so I say let's do it!

16
00:02:20,083 --> 00:02:21,583
This job seems
kinda familiar.

17
00:02:21,666 --> 00:02:24,250
Didn't Gray almost take a job
catching an escaped convict

18
00:02:24,333 --> 00:02:25,708
a little while ago?

19
00:02:25,791 --> 00:02:27,541
This is the same one,
but back then the reward

20
00:02:27,625 --> 00:02:29,500
was only four hundred
thousand jewel!

21
00:02:29,583 --> 00:02:30,625
For some reason,

22
00:02:30,708 --> 00:02:32,458
he's way more valuable
than he used to be.

23
00:02:32,541 --> 00:02:33,916
I wonder who
the client is.

24
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,291
Uh...

25
00:02:35,375 --> 00:02:37,500
Some guy called
Count Balsamico?

26
00:02:37,583 --> 00:02:39,750
That's a pretty
sour name, huh?

27
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:41,583
He'll go great on your salads!

28
00:02:41,666 --> 00:02:43,500
[MACAO] Count Balsamico?

29
00:02:43,583 --> 00:02:45,750
Ya know, rumor has it
that Velveno is gonna make

30
00:02:45,833 --> 00:02:48,666
an appearance at the huge
magical ball that the Balsamico

31
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:50,166
family is throwin' this year.

32
00:02:50,250 --> 00:02:52,416
What the heck are
you talkin' about?

33
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:55,291
They throw a big, fancy
party every seven years.

34
00:02:55,375 --> 00:02:57,250
It's very exclusive; you
gotta be a wizard to even

35
00:02:57,333 --> 00:02:58,708
get through the door.

36
00:02:58,791 --> 00:03:00,875
[WAKABA] The next one's
happenin' this Saturday.

37
00:03:00,958 --> 00:03:02,750
Alright, then let's
crash this rich guy's party

38
00:03:02,833 --> 00:03:05,666
this weekend and walk out
four million jewel richer!

39
00:03:05,750 --> 00:03:06,625
Sounds like a plan!

40
00:03:06,708 --> 00:03:07,750
I'm fired up!

41
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:09,875
This is gonna
be great!

42
00:03:09,958 --> 00:03:12,000
Wait, I just thought
of something, you guys!

43
00:03:12,083 --> 00:03:13,791
If we're gonna go to
this high class ball,

44
00:03:13,875 --> 00:03:16,000
we're all gonna need to work
on our dance moves first,

45
00:03:16,083 --> 00:03:17,625
dontcha think?

46
00:03:17,708 --> 00:03:19,625
Our dance moves?

47
00:03:22,625 --> 00:03:24,166
[HAPPY] The Magic Ball!

48
00:03:25,916 --> 00:03:28,458
[LUCY] Let me show you some
of the basic steps first.

49
00:03:28,541 --> 00:03:29,958
Come here and hold my hands.

50
00:03:30,041 --> 00:03:30,666
[NATSU] Ugh.

51
00:03:30,750 --> 00:03:31,958
This is so embarrassing.

52
00:03:36,041 --> 00:03:37,833
I don't understand
this at all.

53
00:03:37,916 --> 00:03:39,291
What are they
doing again?

54
00:03:39,375 --> 00:03:40,916
It's called
ballroom dancing.

55
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,291
It's super weird.

56
00:03:42,375 --> 00:03:43,541
What's it for?

57
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:45,208
Ow!!!

58
00:03:45,291 --> 00:03:47,000
Uh-oh, sorry
about that!

59
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:50,125
So it's some kind
of foot stomping game?

60
00:03:50,208 --> 00:03:52,083
No, it's more like
the opposite of that.

61
00:03:52,166 --> 00:03:53,833
If you know how
to dance like this,

62
00:03:53,916 --> 00:03:56,333
you can meet a stranger
at a ball and move your body

63
00:03:56,416 --> 00:03:58,250
in perfect rhythm with theirs.

64
00:03:58,333 --> 00:03:59,916
[KINANA and ROMEO]
That sounds cool!

65
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:00,833
Hey!

66
00:04:00,916 --> 00:04:01,833
What are you two
doing over here,

67
00:04:01,916 --> 00:04:03,208
playing some kinda
game or somethin'?

68
00:04:03,291 --> 00:04:04,458
It's not a game, doofus!

69
00:04:04,541 --> 00:04:06,458
Let me play
a round with ya!

70
00:04:06,541 --> 00:04:08,625
[LUCY] You just
got disqualified!

71
00:04:10,333 --> 00:04:11,708
[JUVIA] How dare he?

72
00:04:11,791 --> 00:04:13,541
Using his seductive
dance moves to flirt

73
00:04:13,625 --> 00:04:15,541
with other girls behind my back.

74
00:04:15,625 --> 00:04:17,750
If you have to strip down
to dance with Gray,

75
00:04:17,833 --> 00:04:19,333
I am more than willing!

76
00:04:20,333 --> 00:04:21,000
[ERZA] Well...

77
00:04:21,083 --> 00:04:22,250
you may not be aware,

78
00:04:22,333 --> 00:04:24,375
but in certain circles,
I was once known as

79
00:04:24,458 --> 00:04:25,750
the "dancing demon."

80
00:04:25,833 --> 00:04:27,166
You were?

81
00:04:27,250 --> 00:04:28,500
[ERZA] Requip!

82
00:04:28,583 --> 00:04:29,416
Ready?

83
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:30,625
Let's dance!

84
00:04:30,708 --> 00:04:32,708
Nah, I don't think
I'm quite ready yet.

85
00:04:32,791 --> 00:04:34,000
Don't be so foolish!

86
00:04:34,083 --> 00:04:35,250
All you need

87
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:36,791
is spirit!

88
00:04:38,958 --> 00:04:40,125
[NATSU] I'm gonna hurl!

89
00:04:40,208 --> 00:04:41,875
Well, I guess Erza
was telling everybody

90
00:04:41,958 --> 00:04:43,375
the truth about
her nickname.

91
00:04:43,458 --> 00:04:45,333
Anyone who can make you
that sick has to be

92
00:04:45,416 --> 00:04:46,833
some kind of demon.

93
00:04:46,916 --> 00:04:48,250
[LISANNA] I can
teach Natsu.

94
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:50,208
He'll be cutting a rug
like a pro in no time.

95
00:04:50,291 --> 00:04:52,875
If ya don't mind, I'm gonna
take a break for just a--

96
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:55,875
[LISANNA] Now let your
shoulders relax a bit

97
00:04:55,958 --> 00:04:57,416
but keep your back straight!

98
00:04:57,500 --> 00:04:59,875
[NATSU] This is the worst thing
that's ever happened to me!

99
00:04:59,958 --> 00:05:02,333
How can Natsu be
such a big sissy?

100
00:05:02,416 --> 00:05:03,916
Come on kid, man up!

101
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,000
All right, Elfman.

102
00:05:05,083 --> 00:05:06,375
May I have this dance?

103
00:05:07,625 --> 00:05:10,500
A real man doesn't
get spun around like this!

104
00:05:10,583 --> 00:05:12,333
Ballroom dancing
looks amazing.

105
00:05:12,416 --> 00:05:14,583
I wanna try it, too!

106
00:05:14,666 --> 00:05:17,875
[WARREN] May I
have this dance?

107
00:05:17,958 --> 00:05:19,541
That sounds
delightful.

108
00:05:23,250 --> 00:05:24,541
Oh wow.

109
00:05:24,625 --> 00:05:26,833
Wendy really knows how
to dance, doesn't she?

110
00:05:26,916 --> 00:05:28,458
I don't like her prancing
around with a man

111
00:05:28,541 --> 00:05:29,541
twice her age.

112
00:05:29,625 --> 00:05:30,291
Uh.

113
00:05:30,375 --> 00:05:32,000
May I have this dance?

114
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:35,125
Fine, but just this once.

115
00:05:35,208 --> 00:05:37,291
Maybe we should
try it out, too.

116
00:05:37,375 --> 00:05:39,166
Yeah, it
could be fun.

117
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:45,125
My lady, would you
grant me the pleasure?

118
00:05:45,208 --> 00:05:46,625
But of course, sir.

119
00:05:46,708 --> 00:05:48,208
Awesome!

120
00:05:48,291 --> 00:05:49,541
Think you can just
waltz up and dance

121
00:05:49,625 --> 00:05:50,875
with whoever ya want?

122
00:05:50,958 --> 00:05:51,791
You're just jealous!

123
00:05:51,875 --> 00:05:52,708
And you're crazy
if you believe--

124
00:05:52,791 --> 00:05:53,958
Real cool, dad.

125
00:05:54,041 --> 00:05:54,708
Hey!

126
00:05:54,791 --> 00:05:55,250
Yeah?

127
00:05:55,333 --> 00:05:56,416
What is it?

128
00:05:56,500 --> 00:05:58,708
Just so you know, I
ain't the dancin' type!

129
00:05:58,791 --> 00:06:01,333
Well that's perfect, because
nobody's asking you!

130
00:06:02,541 --> 00:06:04,333
[JET and DROY] Oh Levy,
will you dance with me?

131
00:06:04,416 --> 00:06:05,166
Back off, man.

132
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:06,041
I asked her first!

133
00:06:06,125 --> 00:06:07,416
Nuh-uh, I did!

134
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:08,083
I did!

135
00:06:08,166 --> 00:06:09,083
No, I did!

136
00:06:10,958 --> 00:06:12,416
Okay, fine.

137
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:13,791
If you insist.

138
00:06:13,875 --> 00:06:14,791
Whaddaya talkin' about?

139
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:15,958
I never asked you.

140
00:06:16,041 --> 00:06:18,000
[JET and DROY]
That's so not fair!

141
00:06:18,083 --> 00:06:19,958
I know all about
the magic of dance!

142
00:06:20,041 --> 00:06:22,916
Yeah, that's true, but this
is a little different.

143
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:25,375
[ERZA] Everyone out of the way!

144
00:06:26,375 --> 00:06:28,750
[LUCY] Wow, this private lesson
turned into a full on

145
00:06:28,833 --> 00:06:30,333
dance party.

146
00:06:30,416 --> 00:06:31,875
Wait.

147
00:06:31,958 --> 00:06:35,125
Am I seriously the only one here
that doesn't have a partner?

148
00:06:35,208 --> 00:06:36,666
You raaang, my lady?

149
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:38,791
Nope, I sure didn't!

150
00:06:38,875 --> 00:06:40,958
[LUCY] I had no idea you were
such an excellent dancer.

151
00:06:41,041 --> 00:06:42,875
[CAPRICORN] To honor your
late mother, I swore an oath

152
00:06:42,958 --> 00:06:45,250
to ensure that you were
brought up to be a lady worthy

153
00:06:45,333 --> 00:06:46,666
of the Heartfilia name.

154
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:47,958
Yeah. okay.

155
00:06:48,041 --> 00:06:49,750
but this seems a bit much.

156
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:51,750
Let's start the
daaance from the top.

157
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:53,916
Do try to get it
right this time.

158
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:02,833
[NARRATOR] This ostentatious
palace is the home of

159
00:07:02,916 --> 00:07:05,000
Count Balsamico.

160
00:07:05,958 --> 00:07:07,416
[ALL] We're here!

161
00:07:07,500 --> 00:07:08,916
[LUCY] This definitely looks
like the kinda place

162
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,583
that would have a magical ball.

163
00:07:11,625 --> 00:07:13,416
[GRAY] I didn't realize
it was so far away.

164
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:16,125
[ERZA] a small price to pay
for the chance to dance.

165
00:07:16,208 --> 00:07:18,000
You do remember that
we came all this way to catch

166
00:07:18,083 --> 00:07:20,041
an escaped convict, right?

167
00:07:22,333 --> 00:07:24,250
Um, you're a little early.

168
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:25,833
[WARREN, telepathic scream]
Whoa, what a fox!

169
00:07:25,916 --> 00:07:27,375
Was it really
necessary to scream

170
00:07:27,458 --> 00:07:29,208
that inside
of my head?

171
00:07:29,291 --> 00:07:31,083
[GRAY] We're here
to see the count.

172
00:07:31,166 --> 00:07:32,583
[GIRL] Yes,
of course you are.

173
00:07:32,666 --> 00:07:36,250
My name is Aceto and my
father is Count Balsamico.

174
00:07:36,333 --> 00:07:37,958
[WARREN] She's too pretty
to have such an ugly name.

175
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:40,458
[ALL] Everybody
can hear you, ya idiot!

176
00:07:40,541 --> 00:07:43,083
My name is Natsu
and we're with Fairy Tail.

177
00:07:43,166 --> 00:07:44,875
We've come here
concerning the job request

178
00:07:44,958 --> 00:07:47,958
that your father posted
in our guild hall.

179
00:07:48,041 --> 00:07:50,541
In that case, I'll
take you right to him.

180
00:07:50,625 --> 00:07:52,083
Please, follow me.

181
00:07:55,041 --> 00:07:57,000
Welcome, and thank
you for taking my request.

182
00:07:57,083 --> 00:08:00,250
I am indeed Count Balsamico!

183
00:08:00,333 --> 00:08:01,416
This guy is hilarious!

184
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:02,666
He's got a sour name!

185
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:04,125
And a sour
face to match!

186
00:08:04,208 --> 00:08:06,833
Don't screw this
up for me, okay?

187
00:08:06,916 --> 00:08:08,625
[BALSAMICO] Let me get
straight to the matter.

188
00:08:08,708 --> 00:08:10,666
I want you to know
there is more to the story

189
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:13,041
than what was
written on the flyer.

190
00:08:13,125 --> 00:08:14,791
Please, go on.

191
00:08:14,875 --> 00:08:16,750
I am exceedingly
concerned for the well being

192
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:19,666
of my precious daughter, who
means more than the world to me.

193
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:21,333
Then why'd you give
her such a silly name?

194
00:08:21,416 --> 00:08:22,750
It's a lovely name!

195
00:08:22,833 --> 00:08:25,750
I apologize and
please, continue Sir.

196
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:28,208
[BALSAMICO] The ball being held
this evening is very special,

197
00:08:28,291 --> 00:08:31,583
for it is tonight that her
future husband shall be chosen.

198
00:08:31,666 --> 00:08:33,750
Yeah, that is
a pretty major deal!

199
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:36,125
[BALSAMICO] Once every seven
years, our family brings out

200
00:08:36,208 --> 00:08:38,041
an extremely precious ring.

201
00:08:38,125 --> 00:08:39,708
A ring that has
been passed down through

202
00:08:39,791 --> 00:08:43,000
the Balsamico family line
for countless generations!

203
00:08:43,083 --> 00:08:44,916
And you're afraid that
Velveno is gonna come here

204
00:08:45,000 --> 00:08:46,875
and try to steal it from you?

205
00:08:46,958 --> 00:08:48,583
[BALSAMICO] I'm
absolutely certain of it,

206
00:08:48,666 --> 00:08:51,125
since he tried and
failed seven years ago.

207
00:08:52,250 --> 00:08:54,166
But he did ruin
the ceremony to choose

208
00:08:54,250 --> 00:08:55,625
my daughter's husband.

209
00:08:55,708 --> 00:08:58,750
I see, but given his
"unique" appearance.

210
00:08:58,833 --> 00:09:00,708
Wouldn't sneaking in
undetected prove to be

211
00:09:00,791 --> 00:09:02,541
a bit difficult for him?

212
00:09:02,625 --> 00:09:04,875
He is very skilled in
both transformation magic

213
00:09:04,958 --> 00:09:06,250
and "Magical Drain."

214
00:09:06,333 --> 00:09:07,666
"Magical Drain"?

215
00:09:07,750 --> 00:09:08,875
What the heck's that?

216
00:09:10,375 --> 00:09:11,916
[BALSAMICO] It allows him
to temporarily copy the type

217
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,958
of magic used by anyone
he comes into contact with.

218
00:09:15,041 --> 00:09:16,833
It's very dangerous indeed.

219
00:09:16,916 --> 00:09:19,750
Aw man, I wanna use magic
like that sometime!

220
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:22,083
I entrust full safety
of the ring to you.

221
00:09:22,166 --> 00:09:24,916
Work together and make sure
he fails to snatch it again.

222
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,708
And what's more, I want
you to capture him

223
00:09:26,791 --> 00:09:29,583
and put him back behind bars
where he rightfully belongs!

224
00:09:29,666 --> 00:09:31,416
We'll catch this
clown for ya.

225
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:33,333
Yes. We will, Sir.

226
00:09:33,416 --> 00:09:34,875
Uh, just one more thing.

227
00:09:34,958 --> 00:09:37,083
The flyer mentioned a
certain reward if we were

228
00:09:37,166 --> 00:09:38,375
to catch him for you?

229
00:09:38,458 --> 00:09:39,666
That's correct,

230
00:09:39,750 --> 00:09:41,958
four million jewel in
cash for his capture.

231
00:09:42,041 --> 00:09:43,541
Oh yeah!

232
00:09:43,625 --> 00:09:44,500
Cash is king!

233
00:09:44,583 --> 00:09:46,000
Let's do this!

234
00:09:52,458 --> 00:09:53,583
All done, baby.

235
00:09:53,666 --> 00:09:55,000
Thank you.

236
00:09:55,083 --> 00:09:56,541
But what'll happen if I'm
so beautiful that someone

237
00:09:56,625 --> 00:09:58,666
proposes to me instead?

238
00:09:58,750 --> 00:10:00,333
[ERZA] Ready to
get to work, Lucy?

239
00:10:01,458 --> 00:10:02,708
Holy fashion
statement,

240
00:10:02,791 --> 00:10:04,666
you are definitely
not playing around!

241
00:10:04,750 --> 00:10:07,041
Although we've come here
strictly for business purposes,

242
00:10:07,125 --> 00:10:09,666
we have to look the part
of elegant partygoers.

243
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:13,916
[WENDY] So, uh, do I look okay?

244
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:14,791
Okay?

245
00:10:14,875 --> 00:10:16,666
You look absolutely adorable.

246
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:17,500
Thank you.

247
00:10:17,583 --> 00:10:19,458
I never dress up like this.

248
00:10:20,583 --> 00:10:21,750
Now then!

249
00:10:21,833 --> 00:10:23,875
The curtain is rising
on the magical ball,

250
00:10:23,958 --> 00:10:26,500
so let's take our places
on the dance floor!

251
00:10:26,583 --> 00:10:28,375
I haven't seen her this
worked up since we were

252
00:10:28,458 --> 00:10:29,958
in that weird
play together.

253
00:10:30,041 --> 00:10:32,541
Okay, I'll try not
to mess this up.

254
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:35,666
[WENDY] I wonder if I should
cast a Troia spell on Natsu

255
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:37,166
before we get started.

256
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:46,666
[ERZA, telepathicly] Warren,
